          <long_desc isprivate="0">
            <commentid>12422</commentid>
            <who name="Alexander Steitz">alexander.steitz</who>
            <bug_when>2009-09-18 16:00:22 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>At the moment the wiki search is looking for every wiki page and sometimes (depending on the search term) one gets multiple results for multiple branches (e.g. 0.7.x and 0.8.x) which can only be distinguished by the URL (hovering over the link) not by name of the link itself. This can be irritating for many users.

Offer a search which can be narrowed to the current release or modify the search to only operate at the current release docs (which can be extended to search all wiki pages).</thetext>
          </long_desc>
          <long_desc isprivate="0">
            <commentid>23043</commentid>
            <who name="Andreas Ecker">qooxdoo</who>
            <bug_when>2011-03-03 13:46:42 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>This should be fixed by now (it was fixed in a similar way before): whenever you submit the search field on the homepage/startpage, it will present the hits for the homepage only. In a selectbox you&#39;re able to switch to the results for specific releases or the news stream. Since qooxdoo 1.2 the manuals are no longer maintained in the wiki and come with there (version-)specific search anyway.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
